To save text to a local file in JavaScript, you can use File API and Blob objects. Here's a simple example:

```javascript
// Create the file content
var text = "Hello world!";

// Create a new blob from the content
var blob = new Blob([text], { type: 'text/plain' });

// Create a URL for the blob
var url = window.URL.createObjectURL(blob);

// Download the file by creating an anchor element and simulating a click
document.createElement('a').download = 'example.txt';
document.createElement('a').href = url;
document.createElement('a').click();
```

This will create a new file with the content "Hello world!" and download it automatically in the user's browser.

Remember, this code is meant to be run on the client side (in the user's browser), not on the server side or within Node.js.
